description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;NHSX is leading the largest digital health and social care transformation programme in the world and has been created to give staff and citizens the technology they need.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a joint unit made up of colleagues in the Department of Health and Social Care (DHSC) and NHS England and Improvement (NHSE/I) and will harness the best expertise from industry, the NHS, Government and the health and care sectors. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;NHSX will deliver the Health Secretary’s Tech Vision&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;, building on the NHS Long Term Plan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. We will speed up the digital transformation of the NHS and social care. We have set ourselves five missions, which are focused on how we can make things better for patients and staff.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NHSX AI Team is responsible for leading the delivery of the programmes under the NHS AI Lab as part of the Strategy and Policy Directorate in NHSX.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team works alongside the Accelerated Access Collaborative, National Institute of Health Research, Office for Life Sciences, health regulators and other partners to deliver projects aimed at accelerating the adoption of&lt;br /&gt;safe and effective AI technology into the health and care sectors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note this role is a fixed term contract as part of a limited term project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: NHS AI Lab&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: ailab@nhsx.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
